        "types_of_clay_block_MAY3B3": {
          "type": "types-of-clay-block",
          "name": "Types of Clay Block",
          "settings": {
            "slide_1_title": "Bentonite",
            "slide_1_subtitle": "Montmorillonite",
            "slide_1_description": "<p>Bentonite, also commonly known as <em>Green Alkaline Healing Clay</em>, or <em><strong>Green Desert Calcium Bentonite</strong></em>, is in a class of clays known as Smectites, a class of swelling clays.</p><p>Smectite is derived from the ancient Greek word <em><strong>σμηκτρίς</strong></em><strong>s </strong>or<strong> </strong><em><strong>mektris</strong></em> meaning, '<em>earth that has the property of cleaning</em>'</p><p>As with any mineral, the quality of clay deposits vary, and the mineral content of any given \"Bentonite\" is also quite different depending on the source.</p><p>Different forms of bentonite may have different properties, such as:</p><ul><li><em><strong>Sodium Bentonite</strong></em></li><li><em><strong>Calcium Bentonite</strong></em></li><li><em><strong>Magnesium Bentonite</strong></em></li></ul>",
            "slide_1_button_text": "Shop now",
            "slide_1_button_link": "shopify://products/red-desert-calcium-bentonite",
            "slide_2_title": "Illite",
            "slide_2_subtitle": "French Green Clay",
            "slide_2_description": "<p><strong>Montmorillonite</strong>: French green healing clay (also a smectite) closely related to bentonite.</p><p><br/><strong>Illite: </strong>Non-swelling green healing clay (mica) known to have potent healing properties.</p><p>Utilizing the curative power of the Earth in practices such as Pelotherapy should, we believe, truly be considered a lifestyle modification; it should be adopted as an integral part of healthy living. There is no substitute for the benefits that quality healing clays can provide both in and on the body. We cordially invite you to view what we have discovered over the last several years of research.</p>",
            "slide_2_button_text": "Explore",
            "slide_2_button_link": "shopify://products/illite-french-green-clay",
            "slide_3_title": "Salts",
            "slide_3_subtitle": "Mineral",
            "slide_3_description": "<p><strong>Magnesium Chloride</strong>: Derived from sea salts, Magnesium Chloride Flakes are the 100% pure and natural way to replenish the body's stores.</p><p><strong>Himalayan Pink Salt: </strong>Straight from the foothills of the world's highest mountain range, Himalaya Pink Salt is believed to be the purest of the salts, delivering over 84 minerals and trace elements.</p><p><strong>Dead Sea Salt: </strong>Procured from the saltiest and deepest sea in the world, Dead Sea Salt is world re-known for being a great anti-inflammatory and skin rejuvenator.</p>",
            "slide_3_button_text": "Learn more",
            "slide_3_button_link": "shopify://products/triple-blend-varieties",
            "title_size": 40,
            "subtitle_size": 20,
            "description_size": 16,
            "button_size": 16,
            "title_color": "#7b2b26",
            "subtitle_color": "#7b2b26",
